# Purpose INDEX

List of Purpose notebooks (one parent research thesis per file), with their
per-H verdicts and the Purpose-level verdict. `scripts/new_purpose.py` adds
new entries automatically.

## Entries

| purpose_id | target_sub_claim_id | Purpose (parent thesis, one line) | Hypotheses (H<id>: verdict) | Notebook status | Purpose-level verdict (one line) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| pur_001 | G1.0 (foundation) | (example) Data universe is defined | H1: foundation | done | supported — universe of N instruments × T period defined; data hashes recorded |
| pur_002 | G1.1 | (example) Top-3 PCA factors carry IC ≥ 0.03 on test | H2: supported · H3: rejected · H4: parked | done | partial — IC ≥ 0.03 holds on val, fails on test (binding axis: regime composition change) |
| pur_003 | G1.2 | ... | ... | in-progress | (pending) |

## Notebook-status legend (per notebook)

- `planned`: Purpose stated, notebook not created
- `in-progress`: notebook created, at least one H not yet at a final per-H verdict
- `done`: every H inside the notebook is at a final per-H verdict (supported / rejected / partial / parked) AND the Purpose-level verdict on the parent thesis is recorded (supported / refuted / partial / refuted-as-stated)
- `parked`: blocked on upstream dependency
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing; reason recorded in decisions.md

A notebook is `done` only when the parent thesis itself has received a
Purpose-level verdict — not when one specific H is final, and not when
the per-H verdicts are all in but the Purpose-level verdict is missing.

## Order

Sequential numbering, but dependencies (upstream Purposes first) take precedence.
Each notebook states its upstream dependencies in its "Upstream dependencies"
section.
